-- StanChart Said to Give Jonsson, Arnaudy Capital Markets Roles
-- B y   W e n d y   M o c k
-- 2012-05-04T11:26:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-04/stanchart-said-to-give-jonsson-arnaudy-capital-markets-roles.html
Standard Chartered Plc (STAN)  has assigned
responsibility for capital markets in Asia to Cristian Jonsson
and Anthony Arnaudy, said two people familiar with the matter
who declined to be identified because the details are private.  Jonsson, who is global head of syndicate, is taking on the
responsibility for capital markets in Southeast Asia. His title
will not change, the people said.  Arnaudy will take on responsibility for capital markets in
Northeast Asia, the people said. He remains head of debt capital
markets in Northeast Asia, they said.  Hsueh Mei Tan, a Singapore-based spokeswoman for the bank,
wasnâ€™t immediately available to comment on the new
responsibilities.  To contact the reporter on this story:
